docs.lead_paragraph: UP a flight of stairs above a dark and dusty little West Street ship chandlery, within earshot of the water front and the drays that rumble along it, is the study and office of a priest. It is no tapestry-hung retreat, no cloistered sanctuary, yet in the eye of West Street that little room is sacrosanct.

headline.main: FIGHTING FATHER MAGRATH OF THE WATER FRONT; Adventures Are Plentiful in the Work of This Picturesque Worker Among the Seamen, and He Does Not Hesitate to Use Hard Fists When Necessary to Enforce Right.
